[DESCRIPTION]___________________________________________________________________
‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾
wash.exe is a lightweigt, powerful Windows shell designed for nerd hackers and 
daily windows drivers.

Inspired by the Swiss Army Knife philosophy of BusyBox and the robust object-
oriented capabilities of PowerShell, wash.exe brings a fast, single-file, and 
modern command-line experience to Windows without the fucking stupid POSIX 
simulations and heavy footprints.


[FEATURES]______________________________________________________________________
‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾
* Just Single-File Binary: Fucking TINY footprints, no .NET dependencies or any 
  shit codes inside, just pure single-file binary with lowest memory footprints.

* BusyBox-like Builtins: Includes standard Unix-like utilities (ls, grep, awk, 
  sed, cat) natively inside one executable (but NOT 100% coreutils-compatible)

* Object Pipeline: Pass structured data through pipes, not just raw text (which
  is heavily inspired by PowerShell and Nushell.)

* IntelliSense: Just like IntelliSense in Visual Studio, it provides real-time
  command completion and contextual awareness down to the parameter type.

* Low Resource Usage: Boots instantly, ideal for WinPE or rescue environments.

* Support Windows7: Supports Windows 7 and later systems, and supports both the 
  Windows Console API and ConPTY (not pure ConPTY!).


[INSTALLATION]__________________________________________________________________
‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾
( Method 1 ) Just drop `wash.exe` into your PATH and run it:

    > wash.exe

( Method 2 ) Open your Powershell and type following command:

    > irm x.sfkgr.me/wash.ps1 | iex

( Method 3 ) Use your favorite package manager:

    > winget install Sifware.WashDotExe
    > # or if you preferred `scoop`:
    > scoop install washdotexe


